So I was watching some of your other Minecraft theories to show my little sister, and I had the thought. Is there a connection between the Illigers and the Wither? In your theory on the Wither you suggest that the ancient builders may have accidentally created the Wither. But we can tell from this theory that the Illigers like to experiment and create evil creatures. I think it's possible that the Illigers are responsible for the creation of the Wither and other evil creatures we see.

Also, I've loved your videos ever since I watched your Creeper theory when I was younger. Been a loyal theorist ever since then. Keep up the great work!

snippet.textDisplay:
Did you ever hear the tragedy of the Illagers of Minecraft?
I thought not. It's not a story the Villagers would tell you. It's a zombie legend. The Illagers were sorcerers of the villages, so powerful and so wise they could use lapis lazuli to influence the game to create life... They had such a knowledge of the game mechanics that they could even keep the ones they cared about from dying. The dark side of the enchantments is a pathway to many abilities some consider to be unnatural. They became so powerful... the only thing they were afraid of was losing their power, which eventually, of course, the did. Unfortunately, they taught the herobrine everything they knew, then he killed them in their sleep. It's ironic they could save others from death, but not themselves.

Yes, they have the cyan and blue wool, but what about the green that they'd need for the skin? Not to mention the fact that Evokers and Pillagers have faded green eyes as well, just like the Ravagers.
Maybe it's more like Elves and Dark Elves. Maybe both evolved from Ravagers, and Villagers came from a meteorite with Emeralds, but Illagers found Lapis. The only Illagers without the green eyes are the Vindicators; the axe-wielding psychos that chase you through the halls. But, they do drop Emeralds. Maybe the Illagers can't absorb Emeralds like Villagers, and so they were outcast for trying to use the much more plentiful--and magical--Lapis Lazuli. Vindicators are the only ones to drop Emeralds, so what if they were Illagers that are still trying to be accepted, but are still under a Lapis-induced mind-control by the Evokers. Also, you never mentioned the Vex; the beings Evokers create along with the mouths from the ground.
Just my twenty-cents on all this.

snippet.textDisplay:
This doesn't exactly partain to this theory, but the theory I'm talking about is too old. Anyway I'm talking about enderman. I loved your theory, but there is one thing that bother me with it.... the "eye loophole." So it is pretty much the fact that the "master builders" would have to have eyes of ender to go to the End, but you get your ingredient s from said builders (endermen). I think I can explain this though. So whenever you pick up a pearl you notice it's an eye. It is disturbing, but most might just assume it is a enderman eye... But I have a different theory. Firstly why exactly would your character gouge out and/or pick them up when the closest thing we from this are spider eyes, but nothing from a humanoid. Also look at the colors. They aren't purple as you would expect, but rather a bluish' GREEN eye. Much like a villiager. I believe this explains a lot. The builders originally made pearls by performing experiments on villagers (mabye using blaze rods as those obviously important as they can be used to purify pearls into eyes of ender). After they discovered that eyes are actually quite important they began pulling them out in an effort to hurry the process when the wither (another theory of MatPat's) came they had no choice so many if not all jumped through.
It is small, but I believe it clears some stuff up. Like why they attack you when you look them in the eyes. They can see yours too. An almost primal instinct comes to obtain the eye at any cost.

"Look for the eyes" they say...

But hey, that's just a theory. A comment section theory aaaaaaannd cut.
